{
  "texts": [
    "The ConvBlock is a combination of a convolution layer and a ReLU activation function, capturing spatial information and introducing non-linearity.",
    "The P_scSE block blends Channel-wise Squeeze-and-Excitation (cSE) and Spatial Squeeze-and-Excitation (sSE) operations.",
    "The cSE focuses on channel interdependencies, providing global context, while the sSE concentrates on the spatial interdependencies of each channel, maintaining detailed spatial information.",
    "Outputs from the cSE and sSE are merged using max-out and addition operations 52 as shown in Fig. 8.",
    "The integration of P_scSE blocks serves a dual purpose."
  ]
}